        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I was working with Zend_Form and I needed to disable the translation for all form's elements.\r\nI tried using Zend_Form::setDisableTranslator but it seems that the propagation do not occur to the elements.\r\nI know I can disable the translation per element, but my first thought about Zend_Form::setDisableTranslator was that it could do the job in a global scope. But checking the source, it not happens.\r\nWhen an element try to get the translator object, it calls Zend_Form::getDefaultTranslator and in this method no check is made to see if \"translatorIsDisabled\", but what I get, is the global instance registered in Zend_Registry.\r\n\r\nIs there a way where I can globally disable Zend_Form's (and all elements) automatic translation?\r\n\r\nIf no... it's a good idea, isn't it?\r\nThe implementation could be done on Zend_Form::createElement, where Zend_Form_Element::setDisableTranslator will be the same of Zend_Form's value only if this option doesn't exists in the options array."
        },
